            "text": "Dragon Quest",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " franchise, which is probably what is saving this review's Final Score from being a five or a six. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Dragon Quest Treasures",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is fine, but it is in no way memorable. It's pacing leads to what often feels like a grind and the weak combat doesn't do enough to dismiss this criticism. That being said, the combat serves its purpose towards what is an addictive gameplay loop amongst its free-roaming action-RPG glory. This spin-off entry is bursting with ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Dragon Quest",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " charm, one that a massive fan like me can appreciate in all its colourful Yuji Horii greatness! So it's clear that I'm of two minds with this one, so a non-commital seven is what it must be from me.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
